John said to him,

00:03:51.104 --> 00:03:52.384
Teacher,

00:03:52.224 --> 00:03:55.904
We saw someone casting out demons in your name.

00:03:55.712 --> 00:03:59.520
And we tried to stop him because he was not following us.

00:03:59.872 --> 00:04:08.672
But Jesus said, Do not stop him, for no one who does a mighty work in my name will be able soon afterward to speak evil of me.

00:04:08.320 --> 00:04:11.776
For the one who is not against us is for us.

00:04:11.456 --> 00:04:17.376
"'For truly I say to you, whoever gives you a cup of water to drink "'because you belong to Christ, then

00:04:17.280 --> 00:04:20.832
But will by no means lose his reward.

00:04:20.960 --> 00:04:22.080
Whoever?

00:04:22.176 --> 00:04:26.528
Causes one of these little ones who believe in me to sin.

00:04:26.528 --> 00:04:32.640
It would be better for him if a great millstone were hung around his neck and he were thrown into the sea.

00:04:32.896 --> 00:04:35.744
And if your hand causes you to sin,

00:04:35.424 --> 00:04:43.424
Cut it off. It is better for you to enter life crippled than with two hands to go to hell to the unquenchable fire.

00:04:43.296 --> 00:04:52.928
And if your foot causes you to sin, cut it off. It is better for you to enter life lame than with two feet to be thrown into hell.

00:04:52.768 --> 00:04:56.512
And if your eye causes you to sin, tear it out.

00:04:56.224 --> 00:05:02.848
"'It is better for you to enter the kingdom of God with one eye "'than with two eyes to be thrown into hell.'"

00:05:02.784 --> 00:05:05.472
Where their worm does not die,

00:05:05.376 --> 00:05:08.064
And the fire is not quenched.

00:05:08.224 --> 00:05:12.320
For every one will be salted with fire. salt is good.

00:05:12.224 --> 00:05:22.272
But if the salt is lost, it's salty. How will you make it salty again? Have salt in yourselves and be at peace with one another.

00:05:21.792 --> 00:05:22.624
another

00:05:24.128 --> 00:05:25.248
Amen.

00:05:25.888 --> 00:05:32.192
In each of these passages, Jesus is inviting us to distrust ourselves

00:05:32.224 --> 00:05:34.464
And to depend upon him.

00:05:34.400 --> 00:05:44.448
to distrust our own ability, our own agenda, our ambitions for ourselves, our antagonism toward others, and our attitude towards sin.

00:05:43.968 --> 00:05:44.512
it.

00:05:44.832 --> 00:05:53.152
First, distrust your ability. Jesus heals a mute and deaf boy with epileptic like seizures.

00:05:52.864 --> 00:05:55.744
brought on by an unclean demonic spirit.

00:05:55.808 --> 00:05:58.432
The father couldn't heal his son.

00:05:58.304 --> 00:06:01.344
The disciples couldn't either.

00:06:01.312 --> 00:06:05.408
Jesus could and did. They asked him, why couldn't we?

00:06:05.216 --> 00:06:08.672
And Jesus says the only way is by prayer.

00:06:08.320 --> 00:06:15.680
you can't think you can you must appeal to god don't trust your abilities trust god.

00:06:16.256 --> 00:06:22.336
The father wanted Jesus to heal, but said, "If you can, if you can."

00:06:22.208 --> 00:06:24.512
As if maybe Jesus couldn't.

00:06:24.384 --> 00:06:27.232
So Jesus said, "If I can,

00:06:27.008 --> 00:06:29.920
All things are possible for the one who believes.

00:06:29.984 --> 00:06:37.184
I mean, he's saying it's not the strength of their faith, but the strength of the one in whom they put their faith that matters. Right?

00:06:37.024 --> 00:06:40.416
The man asks what we all should.

00:06:40.416 --> 00:06:43.808
I believe, Lord, help my unbelief.

00:06:44.832 --> 00:06:47.296
So distrust your ability.

00:06:47.136 --> 00:06:54.272
either to do miracles or trust in the Lord second distrust your agenda

00:06:54.400 --> 00:06:58.656
Then Jesus again foretold his sufferings and death.

00:06:58.560 --> 00:07:00.192
And resurrection.

00:07:00.224 --> 00:07:03.456
And again, the disciples didn't understand.

00:07:03.488 --> 00:07:06.048
