00:07:06.048 --> 00:07:12.320
They were slow to understand, slow to ask for help, committed to their own plans for Jesus, not God's plans.

00:07:12.640 --> 00:07:14.496
How like them.

00:07:14.272 --> 00:07:15.584
we are.

00:07:15.360 --> 00:07:18.720
Faith and unbelief are common.

00:07:18.720 --> 00:07:20.256
To Christians.

00:07:20.576 --> 00:07:26.624
We should pray, Lord, help me align myself with you and your agenda.

00:07:27.552 --> 00:07:28.640
Third.

00:07:28.704 --> 00:07:31.424
Distrust your own ambition.

00:07:32.192 --> 00:07:36.160
But then the twelve were arguing about who is greatest among themselves.

00:07:36.544 --> 00:07:38.784
Here they are. So proud.

00:07:38.528 --> 00:07:41.504
So ambitious for recognition.

00:07:41.440 --> 00:07:44.992
So upside down on the meaning of greatness,

00:07:44.832 --> 00:07:47.104
Jesus sets them straight.

00:07:46.752 --> 00:07:49.248
If anyone would be first

00:07:48.960 --> 00:07:52.032
He must be last of all, and servant of all.

00:07:52.448 --> 00:08:02.496
True greatness, you see, isn't ruling but serving. It doesn't aim high but low. And isn't this why Jesus is pre-eminent in the church, because he came?

00:08:02.016 --> 00:08:03.168
She came.

00:08:02.848 --> 00:08:06.368
Not to be served, but to serve.

00:08:06.048 --> 00:08:08.800
and to give his life as a ransom for all.

00:08:09.760 --> 00:08:19.808
but so invested in themselves are the disciples that they then distrust others who are serving Jesus as if Jesus can't have followers we know nothing about.

00:08:19.328 --> 00:08:22.688
And Jesus says, leave them alone.

00:08:22.752 --> 00:08:24.128
Don't stop them.

00:08:24.896 --> 00:08:31.040
So we should distrust our antagonism of others who are serving him.

00:08:31.840 --> 00:08:35.744
And finally, we should distrust our attitude.

00:08:36.160 --> 00:08:37.664
Towards sin.

00:08:37.728 --> 00:08:40.544
Jesus confronts them about temptation.

00:08:40.928 --> 00:08:49.472
because if you have a high opinion of yourself and want glory on earth, who knows how many little ones you might trample.

00:08:49.280 --> 00:08:51.744
As you climb for glory.

00:08:51.584 --> 00:08:58.816
and how evil that would be, and how deserving of the fires of hell, says Jesus.

00:08:58.560 --> 00:09:08.608
we should be so distrustful of our ability and our agenda and our own ambition and our own antagonism to others serving jesus that we would rather lose our hand

00:09:08.128 --> 00:09:14.944
hand or our foot or our eye, then trample on others and cause them to sin.

00:09:15.392 --> 00:09:20.480
We need his attitude towards saying an invitation to replace ours.

00:09:20.640 --> 00:09:23.040
so that we might say, Lord, keep me.

00:09:22.944 --> 00:09:32.992
From presumptuous sin, may they not rule over me, Lord, spare me from sinning against others, even the least of your children. Lord help me.

00:09:32.512 --> 00:09:35.776
Help me rather to live at peace with them.

00:09:37.152 --> 00:09:38.240
